pl.dahdev.bloomfilters

Class EnhancedDoubleHashBloomFilter<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.dahdev.bloomfilters.AbstractBloomFilter<E>
      • pl.dahdev.bloomfilters.EnhancedDoubleHashBloomFilter<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - - the type of elements in this Bloom Filter.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, BloomFilter<E>

    public class EnhancedDoubleHashBloomFilter<E>
extends AbstractBloomFilter<E>
    Implementation of Bloom Filter using Enhanced Double Hashing.

    A Bloom filter is a space-efficient probabilistic data structure that is used to test whether an element is a member of a set. A query returns either "possibly in set" or "definitely not in set". Elements can be added to the set, but not removed.

    Author:
    Damian Stygar

      • EnhancedDoubleHashBloomFilter

        public EnhancedDoubleHashBloomFilter(double probabilityOfFalsePositives,
                                     int expectedNumberOfElements)
        Enhanced Double Hashing Bloom filter constructor.

        Size of Bloom Filter is estimated from: m = (-n*ln(p))/(ln(2))^2, where m is size of Bloom Filter, n is number of expected elements, p is probability of false positives.

        Parameters:
        probabilityOfFalsePositives - probability of false positives.
        expectedNumberOfElements - expected number of elements to be inserted to Bloom Filter.

      • EnhancedDoubleHashBloomFilter

        public EnhancedDoubleHashBloomFilter(int size,
                                     int expectedNumberOfElements)
        Enhanced Double Hashing Bloom filter constructor.

        Number of hash functions is estimated from: k = (m/n)ln(2), where k is number of hash functions, m is size of Bloom Filter, n is number of expected elements.

        Bits per element are estimated from: pbs = m/n, where m is size of Bloom Filter, n is number of expected elements.

        Size of Bloom Filter and number of expected elements should be greater than 0.

        Parameters:
        size - size of Bloom Filter.
        expectedNumberOfElements - expected number of elements to be inserted to Bloom Filter.
